Rating: 4
Tasted exceptional and I will definitely be making again. I like lots of sauce with my mussels so I doubled the amount of wine and cream and added a few more threads of saffron. In terms of preparation, I found the recipe to be more complicated than necessary. Keep it simple by making this a one-pot meal. Soften the leeks in a large stock pot, then stir in a tablespoon of flour which will help thicken the sauce later. Add the wine, mussels, parsley sprigs and saffron; cook on high until the mussels open. Next, stir in the cream then divvy the mussel and broth mixture into individual serving bowls; garnish with minced fresh parsley. As a side dish I served fresh tagliatelle pasta with crushed vine tomatoes, shredded fresh basil, and fresh buffalo mozzarella. Yum.

