Rating: 3
48 mussels is around 3 pounds for me. The saffron taste wasn't strong; next time I'll add a bit of fennel. Definitely do add a generous amount of pepper and salt. I also added 2 shallots, which helped with the texture. You may be tempted to cook the leeks and mussels concurrently. Don't do this! Instead, make sure the leeks get done before the mussels, because you'll want to dump the mussels into the sauce right after the mussels are done so that they don't dry out. I served this on top of store-bought frozen french tries.

